
Prerequisites:
> Running Local nodejs instance. (Find more at (http://nodejs.org))
> Running mongodb instance. (Find more at (http://mongodb.org)) 
> Create database as "nodedb" & collection as users = {email: "test@email.com", password: "password", sex: "male"}
> install mongojs, a nodejs module for mongodb as follows
	npm install mongojs

Locate this 'nodejs-mongoapp' folder & run below command in shell prompt:	
	node helloworld.js
	